Title: Derived categories of sheaves: a skimming Abstract: These lecture notes were prepared for the workshop ``Algebraic Geometry:
Presentations by Young Researchers'' in Snowbird, Utah, July 2004, and for the
autumn school in Lukecin, Poland, September 2004. In six lectures I attempted
to present a non-technical introduction to derived categories of sheaves on
varieties, including some important results like:
  -- the description of the derived category of P^n;
  -- Serre duality;
  -- the Bondal-Orlov result about derived categories of varieties with ample
or antiample canonical class;
  -- the Mukai-Bondal-Orlov-Bridgeland criterion for equivalence;
  -- equivalences for K3 surfaces and abelian varieties;
  -- invariance of Hochschild homology and cohomology under derived
equivalence.
